ypg.erl - Version 1.0
==============
a modified version of ymnesia.erl to work with postgresql

ymnesia.erl is found in the yaws source

yaws, erlang based web server, is found at:

http://yaws.hyber.org/

ypg uses ajax to show results of table searches

Setup
==============
In the yaws.conf, add the appmods line for ypg:

<server localhost>
        port = 8080
        listen = 127.0.0.1
        docroot = /usr/local/var/yaws/www
        appmods = <ypg, ypg>
        appmods = <cgi-bin, yaws_appmod_cgi>        
</server>

Requirements
==============

1. jquery
2. http://code.google.com/p/erlang-psql-driver/
3. create ypg.hrl with this information filled out properly:

-define(HOST, "localhost").
-define(DB, "").
-define(USERNAME, "").
-define(PASSWORD, "").
-define(JQUERY, "/static/jquery-1.4.2.min.js").